1
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:12,733
Don't go near me!

2
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,467
I might accidentally stab
Mookie!

3
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:15,967
Please stop!

4
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:16,933
You have a twin!

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,400
What a shame!

6
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:20,133
There's two of you
in this world?

7
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:20,867
Go ahead!

8
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,100
- Sis!
- Mookie!

9
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:26,800
Mookie!

10
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:28,267
I'm coming with you.

11
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:31,267
You might be your crazy sister's
accomplice.

12
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:33,033
Then you might end up
killing us, too!

13
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:34,433
Someone's following us.

14
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:35,667
What?

15
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:37,267
Drive faster!

16
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:39,167
Hurry up!
They're coming after us!

17
00:00:39,233 --> 00:00:40,900
You have nowhere to go, Mookie!

18
00:00:40,967 --> 00:00:44,133
So you might as well accept
that we'll be together forever!

19
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:45,000
No!

20
00:00:46,067 --> 00:00:48,300
You want to be difficult,
don't you!

21
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:49,967
What else do you want?

22
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:51,467
My Mommy Emma!

23
00:00:54,833 --> 00:00:55,867
No!

24
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:33,300
You won't be seeing her ever
again!

25
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:36,433
Don't you realize
what's going on, Mookie?

26
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:38,667
She caused all this mess.

27
00:01:38,733 --> 00:01:39,567
No!

28
00:01:39,633 --> 00:01:41,667
We're in this mess
because of her!

29
00:01:41,767 --> 00:01:43,567
Because she brainwashed you!

30
00:01:43,633 --> 00:01:47,933
You're the reason why I'm always
weak!

31
00:01:49,533 --> 00:01:51,867
The reason why I'm always sick!

32
00:01:51,933 --> 00:01:54,833
The reason why I didn't get
to enjoy my life!

33
00:01:56,333 --> 00:01:58,967
For seventeen years, Mom!

34
00:02:00,133 --> 00:02:03,700
I thought I'd be miserable
all my life.

35
00:02:03,767 --> 00:02:06,300
Imprisoned in our own house!

36
00:02:06,367 --> 00:02:07,933
I thought I would die

37
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:12,467
if I didn't take the medicine
you'd been giving me.

38
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:13,533
Stop.

39
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:16,433
But when I met Mommy Emma,
she gave me hope!

40
00:02:16,533 --> 00:02:18,600
I finally had someone
on my side!

41
00:02:18,667 --> 00:02:20,000
No!

42
00:02:20,067 --> 00:02:22,133
She's the one who comforted me.

43
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:23,167
Stop it!

44
00:02:23,233 --> 00:02:24,967
She treats me like her own
child!

45
00:02:25,033 --> 00:02:25,900
Stop it!

46
00:02:25,967 --> 00:02:29,767
She loves me, and she will never
hurt me!

47
00:02:29,833 --> 00:02:30,600
Stop it!

48
00:02:30,667 --> 00:02:31,800
I said stop it!

49
00:02:31,867 --> 00:02:32,733
Stop it!

50
00:02:35,067 --> 00:02:36,300
Look, Mom!

51
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:39,533
Is that how a mother should
treat her child?

52
00:02:41,933 --> 00:02:47,267
Because a real mother could
never hurt her child.

53
00:02:47,367 --> 00:02:50,500
So go ahead, hit me!

54
00:02:50,567 --> 00:02:52,933
Hurt me, Mom!

55
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,767
Mommy Emma's coming here
to save me anyway!

56
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:01,033
Olive?

57
00:03:07,167 --> 00:03:08,367
Olive!

58
00:03:09,867 --> 00:03:11,067
Mookie!

59
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:17,800
Olive, get out here now!

60
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:21,767
Mookie!

61
00:03:21,867 --> 00:03:22,733
Mookie?

62
00:03:27,133 --> 00:03:28,800
They're not here!

63
00:03:28,867 --> 00:03:30,733
I knew that they were not here.

64
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:33,133
There's no car outside.

65
00:03:34,633 --> 00:03:36,600
This is insane!

66
00:03:36,667 --> 00:03:38,667
She fooled us again.

67
00:03:40,133 --> 00:03:42,000
Or is it you who fooled us?

68
00:03:42,067 --> 00:03:44,400
You brought us here.

69
00:03:44,467 --> 00:03:47,300
Excuse me, can you stop being
pessimistic?

70
00:03:47,367 --> 00:03:50,733
Like you, I'm just trying
to find them here.

71
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:52,567
Can you stop accusing me?

72
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:54,467
What if I'm out of time?

73
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:56,367
I might not find my daughter.

74
00:03:56,433 --> 00:04:00,700
Emma, don't lose hope.

75
00:04:00,767 --> 00:04:02,800
We will find her.

76
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:04,800
Don't worry.

77
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:06,267
How about this.

78
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:10,533
I'll look around to see if she
left a clue.

79
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:12,767
I'm gonna go through her papers.

80
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:14,500
That's right!

81
00:04:14,567 --> 00:04:16,133
Hey, wait.

82
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:18,567
You might try to fool us.

83
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:22,133
Your family has some trust
issues.

84
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,833
Because you are Olive's sister.

85
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:27,667
Let's look outside. Let's go.

86
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:29,533
- Go, look around.
- Okay, let's go.

87
00:04:31,133 --> 00:04:32,300
No!

88
00:04:32,367 --> 00:04:33,367
No.

89
00:04:39,467 --> 00:04:40,200
No.

90
00:04:49,367 --> 00:04:52,533
Hello Astrid, send people
to the ancestral house.

91
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:55,600
I have a good feeling that Emma
and Jade will be there.

92
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,000
Okay.

93
00:04:58,067 --> 00:05:01,133
But what makes you so sure
that they're together?

94
00:05:01,233 --> 00:05:02,933
They don't know each other.

95
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,367
But they have one common
enemy...

96
00:05:05,433 --> 00:05:06,767
And that's me.

97
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:09,000
Knowing Jade, she always gets
involved.

98
00:05:09,067 --> 00:05:11,900
So she will be helping Emma.

99
00:05:11,967 --> 00:05:17,067
Make sure to do everything
to stop them.

100
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:18,567
I'll call you when I need you.

101
00:05:22,267 --> 00:05:25,067
What are you planning to do?

102
00:05:25,133 --> 00:05:26,300
Mommy, no!

103
00:05:27,467 --> 00:05:29,833
I believe that's none of your
business.

104
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:33,533
No! No!

105
00:05:38,467 --> 00:05:39,500
What the heck!

106
00:05:41,467 --> 00:05:43,333
You almost hit me!

107
00:05:44,367 --> 00:05:46,733
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

108
00:05:47,767 --> 00:05:50,433
You leave me with no choice,
Mookie.

109
00:05:51,633 --> 00:05:53,633
- Sorry, Sorry, Mommy!
- Hold her tight!

110
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:55,967
- Sorry, Mommy!
- You, too!

111
00:05:56,033 --> 00:05:57,300
Lock her up in her room!

112
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:58,500
No!

113
00:05:58,567 --> 00:06:03,400
No! Mommy, please! No!

114
00:06:11,767 --> 00:06:12,967
I'm sorry,

115
00:06:13,033 --> 00:06:15,733
but I know nothing about
the Caparas family's property.

116
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:19,400
Olive hasn't told you anything
since she was a child.

117
00:06:19,467 --> 00:06:21,567
No, we're not close like that.

118
00:06:21,633 --> 00:06:22,600
Especially those twins.

119
00:06:22,667 --> 00:06:24,167
Olive is such a brat.

120
00:06:25,533 --> 00:06:27,767
I hope you find your daughter.

121
00:06:31,433 --> 00:06:32,500
I hope we'll find her, too.

122
00:06:33,767 --> 00:06:37,600
I will never forgive myself
if we don't find her.

123
00:06:37,667 --> 00:06:39,800
We've lost her once.

124
00:06:39,867 --> 00:06:44,300
I grieved for her for years.
I can't lose her again.

125
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:53,967
Make sure that she can't escape.

126
00:06:58,367 --> 00:06:59,800
There you go.

127
00:06:59,867 --> 00:07:02,067
She can't escape for sure.

128
00:07:02,133 --> 00:07:03,600
She better not.

129
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:04,633
You can leave now.

130
00:07:16,467 --> 00:07:21,033
I'm sorry if I almost hit you.

131
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:23,667
But it's nothing compared
to what you did to me.

132
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:30,033
After all you've done,

133
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:33,000
do you still wonder why
I don't like you?

134
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:39,067
You're getting on my nerves,
Mookie.

135
00:07:39,133 --> 00:07:41,567
I tried to be nice.

136
00:07:41,633 --> 00:07:45,300
But unfortunately,
you did not like that.

137
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:49,433
So now, we're back
to our normal life.

138
00:07:50,933 --> 00:07:56,000
You are my patient,

139
00:07:56,067 --> 00:07:58,867
and I'm your doctor.

140
00:08:00,033 --> 00:08:05,233
And I will make sure that we'll
be together forever this time.

141
00:08:49,433 --> 00:08:50,533
Oh, my!

142
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:56,000
Why don't people send a message
first before calling?

143
00:08:56,100 --> 00:09:00,400
Why don't you take the call?
It could be important.

144
00:09:00,467 --> 00:09:03,733
Probably not.
It could just be Manny.

145
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:04,500
Manny?

146
00:09:05,667 --> 00:09:06,633
Manny...

147
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:09,000
as in "Manny-ningil".

148
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:12,000
But I don't have "that's
entertainment" to give them.

149
00:09:12,067 --> 00:09:14,067
So, I'll just ignore
the "Judith"

150
00:09:16,633 --> 00:09:18,867
Manny?

151
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:20,433
That's entertainment?

152
00:09:21,933 --> 00:09:23,167
Judith?

153
00:09:23,233 --> 00:09:26,067
Oh, poor you, you don't know
anything.

154
00:09:26,133 --> 00:09:28,200
Manny... "Manny-ngingil"
meaning debt collector.

155
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:32,800
"That's entertainment" meaning
money I didn't have.

156
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:33,333
So I'll just ignore Judith,
meaning due date.

157
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,367
I can't pay them,

158
00:09:34,433 --> 00:09:35,833
so I'll have to ignore
the due date of my bill.

159
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:38,100
So, I'm ignoring the call.

160
00:09:39,867 --> 00:09:41,600
I get it now.

161
00:09:43,433 --> 00:09:45,467
Your name is Ligaya, right?

162
00:09:45,533 --> 00:09:48,233
Call me Joy.

163
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:51,500
But we're in the Philippines,
so you can call me Ligaya.

164
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:54,833
Mommy, I'll get out
of this place.

165
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:56,333
Just wait and see.

166
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:10,200
When I was young,
I pretended to be brave.

167
00:10:10,267 --> 00:10:11,333
Why?

168
00:10:12,767 --> 00:10:17,267
Because no one else would
help me but myself.

169
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:22,500
I want you to be brave, too.

170
00:10:22,567 --> 00:10:29,000
Because I won't always be there
to help you.

171
00:10:29,067 --> 00:10:34,433
I know it's not easy,
but you have to be brave.

172
00:10:37,667 --> 00:10:40,333
You're my stronghold,
Mommy Emma.

173
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:43,200
You're the reason why
I learned to fight.

174
00:10:44,900 --> 00:10:46,667
I must stay strong.

175
00:10:46,733 --> 00:10:48,933
I need to get out of this place.

176
00:11:01,133 --> 00:11:04,200
We were so cute in this picture.

177
00:11:04,267 --> 00:11:06,633
So cute!

178
00:11:13,633 --> 00:11:14,667
You're right.

179
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:18,467
You both look cute.

180
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:24,267
It reminds me of my twins.

181
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:28,400
Twins?

182
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:30,867
Emma has a twin?

183
00:11:30,933 --> 00:11:34,067
Oh, no.

184
00:11:34,133 --> 00:11:39,267
But my firstborns are twins.

185
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:41,700
They're a year older than Emma.

186
00:11:45,767 --> 00:11:47,167
Where are they now?

187
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:50,467
They've been gone
for a long time.

188
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:58,967
My condolences, Ligaya.

189
00:12:04,367 --> 00:12:07,967
Thank you, but I hope
they're not dead.

190
00:12:09,867 --> 00:12:15,800
I mean, I don't know
if they're dead or alive.

191
00:12:19,067 --> 00:12:20,267
Okay, hear me out.

192
00:12:21,933 --> 00:12:23,600
I was a negligent mother.

193
00:12:24,867 --> 00:12:27,000
I'm useless.

194
00:12:27,067 --> 00:12:34,567
I can't take care of them,
so I gave them up for adoption.

195
00:12:37,933 --> 00:12:46,267
But you know what,
I think you're the same age.

196
00:12:49,133 --> 00:12:51,767
When I saw you with Olive,

197
00:12:53,067 --> 00:12:54,367
I thought...

198
00:12:56,467 --> 00:12:57,933
What is it?

199
00:13:04,967 --> 00:13:07,333
When I saw you with Olive,

200
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,067
I thought...

201
00:13:12,233 --> 00:13:13,433
What is it?

202
00:13:32,267 --> 00:13:34,133
I'm such a fool.

203
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:36,933
I'm so stupid. Get a hold
of yourself, Ligaya.

204
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:40,333
I'm sorry,

205
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:46,767
I was reminded of my twins
when I saw you with Olive.

206
00:13:46,833 --> 00:13:48,367
I'm sorry about that.

207
00:14:18,733 --> 00:14:19,500
What now?

208
00:14:20,767 --> 00:14:24,300
Are you going to let them
take Mookie away from you?

209
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,867
No!

210
00:14:27,967 --> 00:14:28,800
No!

211
00:14:30,467 --> 00:14:31,967
I won't let them!

212
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:36,600
They can't take Mookie
away from me.

213
00:14:36,667 --> 00:14:38,967
I am her mother!

214
00:14:41,467 --> 00:14:42,300
Good!

215
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:51,300
Now, you have to tighten
the reins and control her!

216
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:59,733
Do whatever it takes
to keep her with you.

217
00:15:06,433 --> 00:15:07,067
Yes.

218
00:15:08,367 --> 00:15:09,200
Yes.

219
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:15,933
Good.

220
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:41,367
Are you okay, Jade?

221
00:15:41,433 --> 00:15:42,167
I'm fine.

222
00:15:43,700 --> 00:15:44,767
It's a bit dusty.

223
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,467
Excuse me!

224
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:51,133
Bless you.

225
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:09,400
My babies, I'm sorry this
is all I can give you.

226
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,700
I'm sorry, my babies.

227
00:16:19,767 --> 00:16:25,300
Reggie, please give this
to their adoptive parents.

228
00:16:25,367 --> 00:16:26,733
What's this?

229
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:28,100
It's a letter.

230
00:16:29,233 --> 00:16:32,633
I hope my babies will read
them someday.

231
00:16:38,533 --> 00:16:40,567
Where are you, my children?

232
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,233
If you are still alive...

233
00:16:45,233 --> 00:16:47,200
I hope you can forgive me.

234
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:03,267
Mookie, time to eat.

235
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:11,167
Here.

236
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:15,133
What?

237
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:17,767
You don't want to eat?

238
00:17:19,233 --> 00:17:21,067
Fine, it's up to you.

239
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:22,733
You'll get sick.

240
00:17:25,467 --> 00:17:26,333
Come on,

241
00:17:28,233 --> 00:17:30,300
just one spoonful,

242
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:33,567
say ahh.

243
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:44,600
Mommy, I cooked this for you.
Try it.

244
00:17:55,033 --> 00:17:57,033
What do you think? Is it good?

245
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:02,733
You didn't like what I made
for you.

246
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:04,667
You just pretended that you did.

247
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:11,900
If my mom can make me believe
that she ate what I cooked.

248
00:18:11,967 --> 00:18:13,333
I can pretend, too.

249
00:18:20,633 --> 00:18:21,933
Good girl.

250
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:28,400
Here, I brought you milk.

251
00:18:28,467 --> 00:18:30,367
Cause I know that this is good
for you.

252
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:40,033
Very good, Mookie.

253
00:18:44,933 --> 00:18:46,167
Do you want some more?

254
00:19:00,433 --> 00:19:01,267
Hey,

255
00:19:04,533 --> 00:19:05,467
what is this?

256
00:19:05,533 --> 00:19:07,933
Doctor of Medicine?

257
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:08,867
Oh wow!

258
00:19:10,367 --> 00:19:12,367
Your parents are doctors?

259
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:16,500
What kind of doctor?

260
00:19:16,567 --> 00:19:18,567
Are they pediatricians
or surgeons?

261
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:22,167
They were heart specialists.

262
00:19:22,233 --> 00:19:23,833
Heart specialist?

263
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:25,933
The best in town.

264
00:19:29,567 --> 00:19:33,067
So that's why Olive wants
to be a doctor, too.

265
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:35,567
Oh yes...

266
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:39,933
Wait, how did you know that?

267
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:45,033
Of course, we know everything
that's going on with her.

268
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:48,833
We know that she's not
a real doctor.

269
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:52,133
We also know that she's
experimenting on Mookie.

270
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:53,233
My granddaughter.

271
00:19:56,333 --> 00:20:01,500
She did the same thing with me
to make me dependent on her.

272
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:04,067
Doesn't she realize that
what she's doing is wrong?

273
00:20:04,133 --> 00:20:06,367
Why is she doing that?

274
00:20:08,167 --> 00:20:10,733
I have no idea.

275
00:20:12,100 --> 00:20:16,167
She told me that I'm indebted
to her.

276
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:21,267
Because she got my life together
after she ruined it.

277
00:20:23,033 --> 00:20:25,467
I feel bad for Mookie.

278
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:32,367
I hope she'll stop hurting
Mookie.

279
00:20:35,767 --> 00:20:36,933
This is your favorite.

280
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,333
Cream of mushroom soup. Right?

281
00:20:49,133 --> 00:20:49,967
Yes, Mommy.

282
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:54,400
I missed it.

283
00:20:56,033 --> 00:21:00,367
Do you remember making
this whenever I'm sick?

284
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:04,767
You're always there for me.

285
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:11,100
You just don't appreciate
what I do for you.

286
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:15,967
Because you love someone else.

287
00:21:16,033 --> 00:21:18,400
You have your Mommy Emma now.

288
00:21:18,467 --> 00:21:22,000
That's not true.

289
00:21:25,767 --> 00:21:31,767
I felt guilty when
I tasted the soup.

290
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:37,267
It reminded me of our
happy memories together.

291
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:43,133
I miss you so much, Mommy.

292
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:48,900
Really, Mookie?

293
00:21:51,533 --> 00:21:54,233
And you expect me
to believe that?

294
00:21:55,133 --> 00:22:00,833
Not too long ago, all you talked
about was Emma.

295
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:07,567
You kept telling me
how happy you were with her.

296
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:12,900
That I'm the reason
why you're miserable.

297
00:22:12,967 --> 00:22:14,300
Mommy.

298
00:22:14,367 --> 00:22:18,467
I just said that to make you
jealous.

299
00:22:18,567 --> 00:22:24,200
Because I feel like you don't
love me anymore.

300
00:22:25,967 --> 00:22:27,033
What?

301
00:22:29,033 --> 00:22:31,800
What makes you think
that I don't love you?

302
00:22:34,167 --> 00:22:36,467
Because you were hurting me.

303
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:40,500
But, Mommy.

304
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:43,667
Believe me, I love you.

305
00:22:45,267 --> 00:22:48,033
I want things back to how they
were before.

306
00:22:51,033 --> 00:22:52,533
Just the two of us?

307
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:57,167
Without Emma around?

308
00:22:59,433 --> 00:23:00,567
Yes.

309
00:23:02,467 --> 00:23:04,133
You know what, Mommy?

310
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:07,167
When I was at Emma's house,

311
00:23:07,233 --> 00:23:10,567
I realized that I didn't want
to stay there.

312
00:23:10,633 --> 00:23:12,633
It's dirty and crowded.

313
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:14,267
The bed was stiff,

314
00:23:14,333 --> 00:23:16,000
and they didn't have air
conditioning.

315
00:23:16,067 --> 00:23:18,900
I miss my comfortable life.

316
00:23:18,967 --> 00:23:20,233
I miss my room.

317
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:25,033
And I miss you so much, Mommy.

318
00:23:29,567 --> 00:23:30,967
Mookie.

319
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:47,100
Did you think you could fool me?

320
00:23:48,467 --> 00:23:55,633
It was very clear to me that you
choose Emma instead of me.

321
00:23:55,733 --> 00:23:59,033
No, Mommy.
I'm telling the truth.

322
00:23:59,100 --> 00:24:04,733
I was lying about what I said
with Mommy Emma.

323
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:08,000
I will prove to you that I'm
only telling the truth.

324
00:24:08,067 --> 00:24:09,967
That I am loyal only to you.

325
00:24:10,033 --> 00:24:12,133
That I love no one else but you.

326
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,233
Really?

327
00:24:20,133 --> 00:24:22,300
Right on time.

328
00:24:22,367 --> 00:24:25,067
Astrid just sent me a message.

329
00:24:25,133 --> 00:24:30,000
The bodyguards who will
take care of Emma and Jade

330
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:31,733
are there already.

331
00:24:33,167 --> 00:24:33,833
What?

332
00:24:37,733 --> 00:24:42,067
Manny won't really leave me
alone! What the heck!

333
00:24:43,933 --> 00:24:45,500
Just answer it.

334
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:48,433
I will or else he won't stop
calling.

335
00:24:56,167 --> 00:24:57,200
Ma'am Alice?

336
00:24:57,267 --> 00:25:00,300
Why did you call me?

337
00:25:00,367 --> 00:25:03,933
Ligaya, I have gathered
new information.

338
00:25:04,033 --> 00:25:05,967
What is it?

339
00:25:06,033 --> 00:25:10,233
The couple who adopted
your twins are doctors.

340
00:25:11,867 --> 00:25:12,633
What?

341
00:25:17,100 --> 00:25:22,600
But there are a lot of doctors
here in the Philippines.

342
00:25:22,667 --> 00:25:24,733
What kind of doctors?

343
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:26,833
I know.

344
00:25:28,133 --> 00:25:32,133
They said they were cardio...

345
00:25:33,333 --> 00:25:34,167
Cardio...

346
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:37,133
they specialize in heart
disease.

347
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:45,233
Hey! Who are you?

348
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:46,533
Let me go!

349
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:47,667
Let go of me!

350
00:25:47,733 --> 00:25:49,300
Ligaya, help me!

351
00:25:49,367 --> 00:25:52,667
Ligaya! Help me!

352
00:25:52,733 --> 00:25:53,867
Let her go!

353
00:25:59,567 --> 00:26:00,700
Jade!

354
00:26:00,767 --> 00:26:03,067
That's a shocking revelation!

355
00:26:03,133 --> 00:26:05,200
Are you trying to say that Olive
is your daughter?

356
00:26:05,267 --> 00:26:07,000
I have a strong feeling!

357
00:26:07,067 --> 00:26:09,200
I just left for a second,

358
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:11,700
and you're sending Emma
a message!

359
00:26:11,767 --> 00:26:12,500
Why?

360
00:26:12,567 --> 00:26:14,400
Are you asking her to save you?

361
00:26:14,467 --> 00:26:15,967
Look at this.

362
00:26:16,033 --> 00:26:19,667
This is one of the two necklaces
I gave the twins

363
00:26:19,733 --> 00:26:21,133
before I gave them up
for adoption.

364
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:24,300
We're here to find Mookie
because her life is in danger.

365
00:26:24,367 --> 00:26:27,367
Can we focus on helping her
for now?

366
00:26:27,433 --> 00:26:30,867
Jade may be your sister.
